cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a generic optimization framework for neural architecture search using stochastic relaxation and natural gradient method. It also involves simultaneous optimization of weights and architecture, which is a common topic in machine learning. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed method to image classification and inpainting tasks, which are also common topics in machine learning and computer vision, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and search algorithms, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category as it involves natural language processing tasks such as text classification and language modeling.
